@Teresa 
A RUN-ON sentence would get you an automatic F in Jr Yr English class--it was one of Coach Scott's Four Fatal Errors.  (It is a punctuation error; the use of a semi-colon or just the standard Period and Capital Letter to start the next sentence  would save your hide.)
Grammar and Punctuation are two different things (this aimed at some of the other comments) and both matter.  "Comma splice" is another name for run-on sentence.  One does see it a lot on, for instance, FaceBook.

